// Stored on Tenant so we can re-use the same customer across plan changes\n  // and across the Customer Portal session for managing payment methods,\n  // invoices, and cancellation. Source of truth for subscription state still\n  // lives in billing-service's StripeSubscription model.\n  stripeCustomerId String?\n\n  // Phase 29 — first-run onboarding wizard state.\n  //   onboardingSteps     { branding: ISO, team: ISO, requisition: ISO,\n  //                         rounds: ISO, share: ISO } — completion timestamps\n  //   onboardingDismissedAt set when user clicks \"skip / maybe later\"\n  //   onboardingCompletedAt set when all 5 steps done\n  // Wizard shows on dashboard load when both …DismissedAt and …CompletedAt\n  // are null. Each step writes its own timestamp so we can resume partial\n  // progress if a user closes the browser mid-wizard.\n  onboardingSteps       Json      @default(\"{}\")\n  onboardingDismissedAt DateTime?\n  onboardingCompletedAt DateTime?\n\n  // WF2 — embeddable widget groundwork. The exact set of external origins this\n  // tenant has explicitly authorized to frame /embed/* + call /api/embed/*.\n  // Each entry is a normalized https origin (\"https://host[:port]\", no path).\n  // Defaulted empty => additive, no backfill needed; the actual db-push lands\n  // in WF3, the /embed routes + SDK in WF9. Fail-CLOSED security model: an empty\n  // array means NO external site may frame this tenant, so framing stays denied\n  // until an admin opts a specific origin in. Validated at write time in\n  // branding.ts (URL-parsed, https-only, origin-only — no paths/wildcards).\n  embedAllowedOrigins String[] @default([])\n\n  // WF3 — dashboard/theme defaults groundwork (additive, defaulted so the frozen\n  // v1 demo cannot regress; the actual db-push lands in the migrator-rebuild\n  // recipe, the dashboard renderer + theming layer arrive in later WFs).\n  //   dashboardThemeTokens   the tenant-wide design-token overrides (CSS custom\n  //                          properties / palette) applied to every dashboard for\n  //                          this tenant. Shape: a flat map of token name -> value;\n  //                          {} means \"use the platform defaults\" (no override).\n  //   defaultColorMode       the tenant's default color scheme for new users who\n  //                          have not set a per-user preference. One of\n  //                          \"system\" | \"light\" | \"dark\"; \"system\" follows the OS.\n  //   defaultDashboardByRole maps a role key (ADMIN/RECRUITER/HIRING_MANAGER/...)\n  //                          to the dashboardKey that role lands on by default.\n  //                          {} means \"use the platform default home for every\n  //                          role\"; entries are additive overrides per role.\n  dashboardThemeTokens   Json   @default(\"{}\")\n  defaultColorMode       String @default(\"system\")\n  defaultDashboardByRole Json   @default(\"{}\")\n\n  createdAt DateTime @default(now())\n  updatedAt DateTime @updatedAt\n\n  planChangeRequests PlanChangeRequest[]\n\n  @@index([status])\n  @@index([plan])\n}\n\nmodel PlanChangeRequest {\n  id                String           @id @default(uuid())\n  tenantId          String\n  fromPlan          TenantPlan\n  toPlan            TenantPlan\n  status            PlanChangeStatus @default(PENDING)\n  reason            String?\n  requestedByUserId String\n  requestedAt       DateTime         @default(now())\n  reviewedByUserId  String?\n  reviewedAt        DateTime?\n  decisionNote      String?\n\n  // Phase 33a — super-admin approval gate for paid plans.\n  //\n  // Before 33a: APPROVE immediately flipped Tenant.plan (Phase 22).\n  // After  33a: APPROVE for STARTER/PROFESSIONAL only GRANTS approval —\n  // the tenant must then pay via Stripe Checkout before Tenant.plan flips.\n  // ENTERPRISE keeps the old behaviour (custom contract, no Stripe).\n  //\n  //   paymentMethod    \"STRIPE\"  → requires Checkout completion to activate\n  //                    \"ENTERPRISE_CONTRACT\" → flips on approval\n  //                    \"FREE\"   → downgrade to free; flips on approval\n  //   activatedAt      null until Tenant.plan actually changes. Set by:\n  //                    - tenant-service on approval for ENTERPRISE/FREE\n  //                    - Stripe webhook syncSubscription() for STARTER/PROFESSIONAL\n  paymentMethod String?\n  activatedAt   DateTime?\n\n  tenant Tenant @relation(fields: [tenantId], references: [id])\n\n  @@index([tenantId])\n  @@index([status])\n  @@index([requestedAt])\n}\n",
